                                    "text": "Message from the Head"
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "template": "content",
                                "options": {
                                    "text": "Last month we sent our first construction update, and we hope you enjoyed the information about the initial progress of the gym and theater on our upper school campus. We continue to raise funds for the construction, and we welcome your charitable contributions to support this project.
                                    <br>
                                    <br>
                                    While many of us have been enjoying summer, work has continued on Harker's own version of the “big dig.” Our gym and theater will be partially sunken underground to provide efficient use of space while keeping the buildings' footprints moderate, at the same time maintaining as low a profile for the buildings as possible. Earth-moving machines have been digging down 16 feet, filling 1,900 truckloads with dirt to be hauled away. Read on and click through for more news, photos and video about this amazing project!
                                    <br>
                                    <br>
                                    Chris Nikoloff<br>
                                    Head of School"
                                }
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "template": "grid",
            "options": {
                "columns": [
                    {
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "template": "content",
                                "options": {
                                    "text": "<em>Each month we will focus on a particular feature of the gym and theater project. Our feature of this month is the gym.</em>"
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "template": "header",
                                "options": {
                                    "text": "New gym benefits all"
                                }
                            },
                            {
                                "template": "content",
                                "options": {
                                    "text": "It's easy to see how student athletes will benefit from the new gym, with its regulation-size athletic court, space for multiple teams to practice, and home and visiting team locker rooms. Our students will simply walk across campus for practices and home games, and fellow students will easily be able to root for their classmates in a facility on their own campus.
                                    <br>
                                    <br>
                                        But there are so many ways that all students will enjoy the benefits of this large space. Here's just one example: in the past, school meetings have been held weekly in the old gym. With no bleachers in the old gym, students must sit on the floor. Because space is so limited, there isn't enough room for all faculty to attend. The new gym will be able to accommodate the entire student body and faculty, seated on bleachers on two sides of the gym. 
                                        <br>
                                        <br>
                                        In addition, students of all ages will be able to cheer on athletic competitions, as well as be involved in debate, business and entrepreneurship, and science research events in the new building. The new gym will offer countless ways for our community to come together."
                                }
                            }
